<p>The discovery of the <strong>Fast Fourier transformation (FFT)</strong> =
is attributed to Cooley and Tukey, who published an algorithm in 1965.
But in fact the FFT has been discovered repeatedly before, but the importan=
ce of it was not understood before the inventions of modern computers.
Some researchers attribute the discovery of the FFT to Runge and K=C3=B6nig=
 in 1924.
But actually Gauss developed such a method already in 1805, but never publi=
shed it.</p>
