<p>Here the function <code>inverse</code> computes the modular inverse (see=
 <a href=3D"https://cp-algorithms.com/algebra/module-inverse.html">Modular =
Multiplicative Inverse</a>).
The constants <code>mod</code>, <code>root</code>, <code>root_pw</code> det=
ermine the module and the root, and <code>root_1</code> is the inverse of <=
code>root</code> modulo <code>mod</code>.</p>
<p>In practice this implementation is slower than the implementation using =
complex numbers (due to the huge number of modulo operations), but it has s=
ome advantages such as less memory usage and no rounding errors.</p>
